linhello (0.4.5-1) unstable; urgency=medium

  * `linhello update`: build the Arch native package as an unprivileged user
    instead of as root (makepkg refuses to run as root). When updating from the
    root-owned managed clone the native build failed and the updater silently
    fell back to a from-source install; it now builds as the checkout owner (or
    the sudo invoker) in a user-owned build dir, and surfaces native-build
    failures rather than degrading to source. Arch-only path; rpm/deb unchanged.

 -- wisbendji fimerlus <archledger236@gmail.com>  Tue, 23 Jun 2026 14:00:00 -0400

linhello (0.4.4-1) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Plasma 6 / KDE lock screen + login fixes: the daemon classifies the
    `plasmalogin` greeter (and -greeter/-autologin) as login/unlock; the KDE lock
    screen is wired on Debian (not just Arch); `setup`/`pam enable` and the TUI
    wizard add the user to the `linhello` group so the user-run greeter can reach
    the daemon socket.
  * Close a camera cgroup device boot-race with a udev rule + oneshot that
    refreshes the daemon's device access once the webcam enumerates; reload udev
    rules on install so it takes effect without a reboot.
  * TUI wizard parity with `linhello setup`: install the reseal hook, add group
    membership unconditionally, offer a recovery passphrase, and confirm the
    login password (typed twice) before sealing.

 -- wisbendji fimerlus <archledger236@gmail.com>  Tue, 23 Jun 2026 12:00:00 -0400

linhello (0.4.3-1) unstable; urgency=medium

  * SELinux (Fedora/RPM only): allow the confined daemon to run `busctl` and chat
    with fprintd over the system D-Bus, so the fingerprint capability probe no
    longer floods setroubleshoot with execute denials under enforcing. No code
    change; Debian ships no SELinux policy, version synced with the workspace.

